[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man, 74, struck by lorry on Edinburgh street

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 74-year-old man has been hit by a lorry on a street in Edinburgh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The man was struck on Lanark Road, at the junction with Baberton Crescent, at about 14:45.
His condition has not been revealed.
The road has been closed at the Gillespie crossroads while police investigations continue.
